  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, catalogues that enable external/registered users to add/ propose new semantic artefacts to include in the catalogue (65%) delegate the quality control of these changes to the maintainers/curators of the artefacts.",
    "Indeed, generally, more than half of the analysed catalogues (65%) permit the curation of their data by either the owners of the catalogue or the maintainers of the semantic artefacts.",
    "No catalogue provides both strategies.",
    "This aspect is a positive sign, which shows that most of the catalogues are concerned with guaranteeing a good quality of their data.",
    "All catalogues, with only one exception, provide access with no restriction."
  ],
